Draft Tax Credits and Guardian’s Allowance Up-rating etc. Regulations 2017                  The Committee consisted of the following Members:            Chair: Mrs Anne Main            † Barclay, Stephen (Lord Commissioner of Her Majesty's Treasury)            † Ellison, Jane (Financial Secretary to the Treasury)            † Glen, John (Salisbury) (Con)            † Hart, Simon (Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire) (Con)            † Haselhurst, Sir Alan (Saffron Walden) (Con)            Hodge, Dame Margaret (Barking) (Lab)            † Lammy, Mr David (Tottenham) (Lab)            † McLaughlin, Anne (Glasgow North East) (SNP)            † Mackinlay, Craig (South Thanet) (Con)            † Mackintosh, David (Northampton South) (Con)            Reeves, Rachel (Leeds West) (Lab)            † Reynolds, Jonathan (Stalybridge and Hyde) (Lab/Co-op)            † Shelbrooke, Alec (Elmet and Rothwell) (Con)            † Smith, Jeff (Manchester, Withington) (Lab)            † Stephens, Chris (Glasgow South West) (SNP)            † Swayne, Sir Desmond (New Forest West) (Con)            † Throup, Maggie (Erewash) (Con)            Winnick, Mr David (Walsall North) (Lab)            Marek Kubala, Committee Clerk            † attended the Committee            First Delegated Legislation Committee            Monday 6 March 2017            [Mrs Anne Main in the Chair ]            Draft Social Security (Contributions) (Rates, Limits and Thresholds Amendments and National Insurance Funds Payments) Regulations 2017           4.30 pm        The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Financial Secretary to the Treasury (Jane Ellison)       Share       I beg to move, That the Committee has considered the draft Social Security (Contributions) (Rates, Limits and Thresholds Amendments and National Insurance Funds Payments) Regulations 2017.     Share          The edit just sent has not 